# <Disease Or Finding Name> Figure Evidence

Use this file to track figures and images reviewed while writing a
`clinical-statistical-expert` disease chapter.

Store images locally only when reuse is explicitly allowed. If reuse is not
allowed, uncertain, or limited to source-site viewing, link to the external
source instead of downloading or committing the image.

## Figure Evidence Table

| Figure ID | Source | Figure | Reuse status | Local file or external link | Disease.md section | Clinical point |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
|  |  |  | ok-to-embed / link-only / needs-review / private-review |  |  |  |

## Reuse Status

- `ok-to-embed`: image may be stored locally and embedded with attribution.
- `link-only`: do not store locally; link to the source figure.
- `needs-review`: do not store locally until reuse terms are reviewed.
- `private-review`: keep any local copy out of the public repository.

## Required Metadata

For every figure, record:

- figure ID
- disease
- source title
- source URL
- figure label or number
- figure URL when different from source URL
- license
- reuse status
- clinical point supported by the figure
- disease chapter sections supported by the figure
- local path when stored
- attribution text
- date accessed
- notes or reuse limitations

## Markdown Patterns

### Inline Local Image

Use only when reuse is allowed.

```markdown
![<clinical point>](../assets/diseases/<disease>/figures/<figure-id>.png)

Figure: <clinical point>. Source: <source>. Figure reference: <figure>.
License: <license>.
```

### External Link

Use when local storage is not allowed or not yet reviewed.

```markdown
Figure evidence: [<figure>](<figure-url>) supports <clinical point>.
Image is linked externally because reuse status is `<reuse-status>`.
```

## Helper Command

```text
python -m skillforge figure-evidence <disease> --figure-id <id> --source-title "<title>" --source-url <url> --figure-label "Figure 31" --license "<license>" --reuse-status ok-to-embed --image-path <file> --clinical-point "<clinical point>" --section "<Disease.md section>" --json
```
